{"id":"aldrete_score","version":"0.0.1","templates":[{"id":"aldrete_score","version":"0.1.0"}],"language":"en","updated":"2021-08-17T17:22:24+02:00","authors":[{"name":"Maryam Razavi","email":"maryam.razavi@cambio.se"}],"format":"CambioForm.v1","name":"aldrete_score","guidelines":[{"condition":"consciousness && mobility && breathing && circulation && color","execution":[{"id":"Aldrete_score","version":"1"}]}],"elements":[{"type":"form","children":[{"type":"container","children":[{"type":"row","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"type":"column","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"readonly":false,"hidden":false,"children":[{"text":"## Aldrete Score \n\nAldrete score is a method of clinically assessing the physical status of the patient and whether the anesthetic effect (regardless of administration method) has worn off or not. The evaluation occurs immediately after surgery and then every 1 hour before the patient is deemed as ready for discharge. Consciousness, Mobility, Breathing, Circulation and Color are the five items of Aldrete score.\n\n**Formula: **Addition of assigned points.\n\n**Interpretation: **Results vary between 0 and 10. Patients with scores of 9 and 10 can be safely discharged from PACU. Scores of 10 indicate, according to the original study, a patient in the best condition. Scores of 7 and below come with indication of continuous close observation.","type":"text","size":"m","position":"left"}]}]},{"type":"row","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"type":"column","spanlarge":7,"spanmedium":5,"spansmall":5,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"text":"Diagnosis Review","type":"label","size":"l","hidden":false,"position":"left","readonly":false},{"type":"input-select","label":"Consciousness","name":"consciousness","options":[{"text":"Not responding","value":"at0006","magnitude":0},{"text":"Arousable","value":"at0007","magnitude":1},{"text":"Fully awake","value":"at0008","magnitude":2}],"clearable":true,"display":"buttons","hidden":false,"readonly":false,"required":true},{"type":"input-select","label":"Mobility","name":"mobility","options":[{"text":"Able to move 0 extremities","value":"at0010","magnitude":0},{"text":"Able to move two extremities","value":"at0011","magnitude":1},{"text":"Able to move four extremities","value":"at0012","magnitude":2}],"clearable":true,"display":"buttons","hidden":false,"readonly":false,"required":true},{"type":"input-select","label":"Breathing","name":"breathing","options":[{"text":"Apnea","value":"at0014","magnitude":0},{"text":"Dyspnea","value":"at0015","magnitude":1},{"text":"Able to breathe deeply","value":"at0016","magnitude":2}],"clearable":true,"display":"buttons","hidden":false,"readonly":false,"required":true},{"type":"input-select","label":"Circulation","name":"circulation","options":[{"text":"Systemic BP ≠ 50% of the preanesthetic level","value":"at0018","magnitude":0},{"text":"Systemic BP between 20% and 49% of the preanesthetic level","value":"at0019","magnitude":1},{"text":"Systemic BP ≠ 20% of the preanesthetic level","value":"at0020","magnitude":2}],"clearable":true,"display":"buttons","hidden":false,"readonly":false,"required":true},{"type":"input-select","label":"Color","name":"color","options":[{"text":"Cyanotic","value":"at0022","magnitude":0},{"text":"Pale, jaundiced, blotchy","value":"at0023","magnitude":1},{"text":"Normal","value":"at0024","magnitude":2}],"clearable":true,"display":"buttons","hidden":false,"readonly":false,"required":true}]},{"type":"column","spanlarge":5,"spanmedium":4,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"text":"Recommendations","type":"label","size":"l","hidden":false,"position":"left","readonly":false},{"type":"input-count","label":"Total score","name":"total_score","min":0,"max":10},{"type":"input-text","label":"Interpretation","name":"interpretation"}]}]},{"type":"reset-button","label":"Reset"},{"